AI Software Engineer, Agents and Automation
Location: Melbourne (hybrid) 
Reports to: Head of AI

About Affinda Group
Affinda Group is a fast-growing AI transformation company. We help enterprises automate complex business processes through our agentic AI platform, deliver high-impact AI solutions, and train teams to use AI properly.

The Affinda platform combines advanced language models, retrieval-augmented generation, and configurable workflows so organisations can extract data, orchestrate processes, and embed AI safely into their day-to-day operations.

We are growing revenue at 100% year on year, have 2,000+ customers globally and a team of ~100 people in 10 countries. We are well capitalised and are currently investing in multiple growth engines to accelerate our ambition of becoming an Australian AI company of global significance.

The Role
You'll build AI agents for the Affinda platform. You'll also create the connectors and APIs that let AI automation work across the company.

This role sits between experimentation and production. You'll take rough prototypes and turn them into real, maintainable software. You'll figure out what works, then help the rest of the team adopt it.

This role needs both: real engineering chops and genuine enthusiasm for AI. We're open to mid-level or senior candidates depending on experience. If you tried Claude Code in the first week, or you've built your own MCP server just to see how it works—keep reading.


What makes this role special

Cutting-edge AI work: Build production AI agents—text and voice—that guide users through the app like an expert sitting beside them.

The timing: The company is scaling quickly, and we're rebuilding the platform around AI agents from the ground up. Not bolting them onto legacy systems. That window doesn't stay open long.

Tools for builders: You'll build the internal platforms (MCP servers, connectors, evaluation frameworks) that let the rest of the team build AI features without starting from scratch every time.




Key responsibilities

Design and build AI agents for Affinda. Text, voice, whatever helps users get through complex workflows.

Build our internal agent framework: MCP servers, tool connectors, evaluation patterns. Make it possible for agent complexity to grow without chaos.

Create APIs and connectors that let AI automation plug into the rest of the business—and 

into tools like ChatGPT.

Help engineers get better at AI-assisted development. Refine system prompts, build feedback loops, close the gap between "generate code" and "run, test, see it work."

Turn prototypes into production code. POCs should evolve into real applications, not get thrown away and rewritten.

Ship features in our core stack (Python, Django, Celery, PostgreSQL, Elasticsearch, AWS, React). AI is one part of the solution, not the whole thing.




What you'll bring

Experience: 3+ years building software in production web environments.

Backend skills: Strong Python, experience with Django or a similar framework, and familiarity with background jobs (Celery or equivalent).

AI hands-on: You've built something with LLM agents—at work or on the side. Curious about multi-agent orchestration, MCP servers, and evaluation.

AI-native development: You don't have one way of working with AI—you have several Quick prototypes, structured plans, careful line-by-line work. You match the approach the problem.

Some frontend: You can prototype a React UI when needed. Doesn't have to be your main thing.

Communication: You're good at explaining things and helping others build with AI.




Location
Melbourne strongly preferred. Open to remote for the right candidate. Hybrid for locals; we 
have a good office in the city that people actually like coming to.

How to apply
Please submit your CV and a cover letter.

Salary: Competitive salary plus fantastic company benefits
Ad Text:
Hello. We’re Virgin Australia. We’re the airline that’s always done things a little different. Our way. The Virgin way. We’re on a mission to make flying better than ‘nice’. And to do that, it takes a team of talented people who are passionate about customer experience, doing the right thing always, with a focus on safety – in the air, on the ground and in our workplaces. A team who values real diversity and inclusion, in a big brand with big ambitions.

What you’ll be doing:

You’ll be at the forefront of shaping how AI transforms our business. In this role, you’ll take ideas from concept to reality partnering with stakeholders to uncover opportunities designing intelligent systems that solve complex problems and building solutions that scale. From architecting non-deterministic systems to crafting the “last mile” of data science and engineering, you’ll work across the full stack and lifecycle. You’ll also lead the integration and operation of advanced AI models, including LLMs and agents, ensuring they deliver real impact in commercial environments. 

You’ll be great in this role if you:

Hold a Bachelor’s degree or higher in Computer Science, Software Engineering or Data Science or have equivalent applied experience
Have completed AI systems design courses or specialisations (e.g., deeplearning.ai, fast.ai)
Bring 5+ years of experience designing, building and operating production-grade AI systems
Have 2+ years of experience leading engineering teams
Delivered hands on solutions with LLMs and agentic systems (RAG, tool/function calling, planning)
Implemented MLOps/LLMOps practices: CI/CD for models/prompts, registries, automated evaluations, observability
Worked cross functionally with Product, Engineering, Security, Legal/Privacy and Operations teams.
Are fluent in Python and frameworks like FastAPI / FastMCP
Have experience with LangGraph / LangChain, Databricks, pgvector, and AWS Cognitive Search (or equivalents)
Understand advanced RAG techniques, retrieval strategies, context packing, tool orchestration, safety/guardrails
Know observability practices (metrics, logs, traces) and security/privacy fundamentals (IAM, secrets, network isolation, PII handling)
Thrive in Agile delivery environments owning roadmaps, estimation and stakeholder communication across technical and executive audiences

It’s even better if you also:

Hold certifications in AWS, Databricks, Kubernetes, Terraform/IaC, security or Responsible AI
Have deployed AI solutions on AWS and Databricks (including MLflow/Mosaic)
Bring experience in airline/travel operations or high-growth tech environments
Understand optimisation, operations research, reinforcement learning or simulation
Are familiar with React, TypeScript, experimentation platforms, A/B testing and causal inference at scale
Know FinOps strategies for managing model/LLM usage efficiently
Understand agent-based architectures, embeddings and vector databases
Apply MLOps/LLMOps patterns like CI/CD, registries, automated evaluations and canary/shadow deployments
Have knowledge of AWS cloud concepts for secure, scalable AI workloads
Follow software engineering best practices: testing strategies, CI/CD, code health, design reviews
Understand modern data lakehouse patterns and event-streaming concepts
Stay informed on Responsible AI, safety patterns, model governance and privacy law/data residency considerations

What you’ll get from us:

We’re committed to looking after you, with some of the best benefits and conditions in the industry – including (but not limited to):

Heavily discounted air travel for you and your loved ones (including $1000 worth of travel credits per year)
Flexible working arrangements (including work hours and work from home)
Discounts on travel insurance, car hire, accommodation and experiences worldwide
Discounted Virgin Australia Lounge membership
Hospitality, retail, technology, beauty services and wellness discounts
Wellness support, including the Converge digital wellbeing platform
A comprehensive Employee Assistance Program, which offers confidential coaching and support from qualified professionals for all aspects of life – physical, mental, social and financial
Dress for Your Day – enjoy the freedom to wear whatever is appropriate for the type of work you do and the day you have ahead of you

Equality rules:

We’re all individuals. We love that. That’s why we encourage applications from Indigenous Australians, people with disability, those from diverse cultural backgrounds, our friends in the LGBTQIA+ community, and anyone else who wants to join our family.

Ready to apply? We’re ready to hear from you. Apply now.

EL1 Data Scientist - 12-month contract | Canberra (Hybrid)

We are recruiting an experienced EL1-level Data Scientist to support a Federal Government environment delivering advanced analytics and data-driven insights. This role will suit someone who is comfortable working across complex datasets, building robust models, and working closely with stakeholders to solve real business problems.

You will be responsible for applying machine learning and statistical techniques to a range of analytical challenges, developing models that explain trends and predict outcomes, and translating technical analysis into practical recommendations. The role also involves leading small pieces of work or project streams and supporting capability uplift within the broader team.

This is a 12-month contract role based in Canberra, with flexible and hybrid working arrangements available, subject to operational requirements.

What you'll be doing

Apply data mining, machine learning and statistical techniques to structured and unstructured data.

Build, validate and deploy predictive and explanatory models to address business questions.

Analyse performance drivers and provide evidence-based insights to support decision-making.

Work directly with business areas to understand requirements and explain analytical outcomes in plain language.

Select appropriate modelling approaches and data sources, ensuring data quality and integrity.

Develop dashboards or visualisations using tools such as Power BI or Tableau where required.

Lead small analytics workstreams or project components and manage delivery to agreed timeframes.

Maintain clear documentation of models, processes and outputs to support transparency and reuse.

What we're looking for
You are an experienced data science professional with strong technical skills and the ability to communicate complex ideas clearly. You are comfortable working in regulated environments and take a practical, outcomes-focused approach to analytics.

Essential

Demonstrated experience in data science, analytics and statistical modelling, including machine learning.

Strong skills in Python and/or R.

Experience sourcing, cleaning, transforming and integrating data.

Ability to clearly explain analytical findings to non-technical stakeholders.

Experience leading small projects or workstreams and managing competing priorities.

Understanding of data governance, privacy and security requirements.

Desirable

Experience working in government or other highly regulated environments.

Experience developing dashboards or visual reporting.

Exposure to enterprise or cloud data environments.

Eligibility requirements

Australian Citizenship is required.

Ability to obtain and maintain Baseline security clearance and a National Police Check.

Additional suitability checks may apply.

This role involves working with sensitive data and strict data-handling requirements apply, including no offshore data storage.

How to apply
Please submit your CV along with a short summary outlining your data science experience, key technical skills, and confirmation that you meet the eligibility requirements.

We’re entering a new chapter for Information Technology at Water Corporation as we deliver bold, future-focussed solutions. With the launch of our new Information and Technology Group Operating Model, we’re transforming how we deliver technology services, making them faster, more responsive, and more aligned with the needs of our business and customers.

As part of this transformation, we’re hiring multiple new positions. These roles are key to shaping a vibrant, forward-thinking Information and Technology Group - one that adds real value, delivers better outcomes, and works in smarter, more agile ways. It’s a strategic shift aligned with our organisational strategies, designed to modernise systems, embrace innovation, and create a more flexible, collaborative, and customer-centric IT environment.

If you're equally excited about innovation, transformation, and making a meaningful impact, now is the perfect time to join us.

About the role

We are seeking an experienced Solution Architect to lead the design and governance of enterprise digital workplace and security solutions across the Corporation. This role is critical in ensuring business requirements are translated into secure, scalable, and well‑governed technology solutions that align with enterprise architecture standards, principles and roadmaps.

Working closely with delivery teams, enterprise architects and senior stakeholders, you will help shape solution direction across Microsoft 365, endpoint management, collaboration platforms and identity/security controls, while contributing to long‑term architectural strategy and governance.

Real benefits that matter 

Real flexibility with options to work from home, 9-day fortnight, flexible work hours
An additional 2 well-being days each year
Access to long service leave pro rata after 3 years of service
Generous co-contribution superannuation scheme, which offers up to 16%. This includes an 12% standard employer contribution, plus an additional 2% employer co-contribution that matches your own 2% contribution
Purchase additional leave of up to 12 weeks or work 4 years at a reduced salary and take the fifth year off as paid leave

Discover more benefits we offer to support the unique and individual ways our employees live.

What the role will involve

Contribute to the design of end‑to‑end digital workplace and security solutions by translating business requirements into effective system and technical architectures.
Work closely with project delivery teams to define solution vision, scope and architectural requirements.
Perform solution options analysis and recommend fit‑for‑purpose architectures that balance business outcomes, security, cost and long‑term sustainability.
Ensure all solution designs align with enterprise architecture standards, principles and roadmaps.
Assess and clearly communicate the architectural impact of new solutions during requirements and design phases.
Provide architectural oversight for Microsoft 365 E5 platforms, including Defender, Purview (DLP, sensitivity labels), Conditional Access, and PAM/PIM, ensuring secure-by-default collaboration and compliance.
Lead architectural patterns for Microsoft Intune and SCCM co‑management, ensuring strong device hygiene, compliance and lifecycle management.
Design and govern collaboration platforms including Microsoft Teams, SharePoint and OneDrive, enabling secure collaboration, data protection and controlled external sharing.
Support the secure adoption of new technologies and capabilities, including Windows 11 upgrades and Microsoft Copilot readiness.
Support alignment with cybersecurity frameworks and controls, including Australian Signals Directorate Essential Eight.
Engage with architecture governance forums and contribute to solution reviews, providing expert guidance to inform and sanction architectural decisions.
Communicate solution architectures clearly to business stakeholders, development teams and architectural review forums.
Build consensus across diverse stakeholder groups and support solutions through architecture review and approval processes.
Contribute to the development of strategic program architectures, project portfolio architectures and technology roadmaps.
Collaborate with enterprise architects to evolve architecture standards, principles, guidelines and reference architectures.
Continuously evaluate emerging technologies and recommend improvements or innovations where appropriate.
Maintain solution artefacts within the architecture repository in collaboration with architecture governance teams.

Key skills and experience

Mandatory skills & experience:

Extensive experience with Microsoft Intune MDM and SCCM co‑management in an enterprise environment.
Deep working knowledge of Microsoft 365 E5, including advanced security, compliance and identity capabilities.
Hands-on experience implementing data protection and governance solutions (e.g. DLP, Microsoft Purview).
Strong experience with identity and access security, including Azure AD Conditional Access and PAM/PIM.
Proven ability to design and govern Microsoft Teams, SharePoint and OneDrive with robust data governance and external sharing controls.
Working knowledge of enterprise frameworks such as TOGAF, ITIL and SAFe.
Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to translate complex technical concepts into clear business outcomes.

Desirable skills & experience - The following skills and experience are not essential but will be highly regarded:

Experience with zero‑touch device deployment and full asset lifecycle management.
Strong understanding of Zero Trust architecture and Essential Eight controls, including Microsoft Defender security tooling.
Familiarity with enterprise IP telephony, including Microsoft Teams Calling and/or Cisco CUCM.
Experience designing cloud-native solutions (Azure and/or AWS) and integrating DevSecOps practices into CI/CD pipelines.
Knowledge of virtualisation technologies such as Microsoft Hyper‑V, VDI and AWS WorkSpaces.
Experience managing platform lifecycle in an agile delivery environment (e.g. major Windows upgrades or new platform rollouts).
Relevant security certifications, such as:

v Microsoft Certified: Cybersecurity Architect Expert (MCAE)

v Microsoft Certified: Security Operations Analyst Associate (SC‑200)

v Microsoft Certified: Microsoft 365 Security Administrator Associate (MS‑500)

Apply: If you are interested in the above opportunity, please submit a covering letter and resume that best demonstrates your ability to meet the requirements of the role.

Stacked Farm: Redefining the Future of Vertical Farming

Ready to revolutionize agriculture? Stacked Farm is leading the way in automated indoor vertical farming - driven by innovation, efficiency and sustainability. With proprietary automation technology, we’ve reimagined how leafy greens are planted and harvested: faster, cleaner and greener than ever before.

Recently named 2025 Sustainability Leader by The Australian Financial Review, winning both the Agriculture & Environment category and the title of Overall Innovation Winner. As we continue our rapid expansion with new farms and advanced product lines, we’re reshaping the Ag-Tech landscape.

Why We’re Different

We’ve cracked the code where others have struggled. Our proprietary technology, advanced systems and repeatable processes deliver a scalable and sustainable model, one that’s built to last.

Backed by leading investors in both Australia and the U.S., we have the capital, vision and momentum to scale fast...and smart.

Why Join Stacked Farm?

Working at Stacked Farm means more than just clocking in. It’s a chance to innovate, make an impact and be part of something meaningful:

Shape the Future – Join a company solving some of the biggest challenges in agriculture.

Long-Term Stability – Be part of a proven and well-funded global business.

Collaborative Innovation – Work where your ideas matter and creativity is valued.

Exceptional Benefits – Enjoy great perks including the best coffee in the area, free on-site gym and parking, regular achievement recognition, quarterly team events and monthly birthday celebrations — to name but a few.

About The Role?

Working as part of a small, high-energy team, you will be building and maintaining a modern, complex SCADA system for a cutting edge, environmentally conscious manufacturing facility.  You will develop new features as well as revise and optimise existing production systems. This role requires strong creative problem-solving skills and the ability to write robust, production-grade code for mission-critical systems that must maintain 24/7 uptime. You will collaborate closely with the CTO and multi-disciplined engineering team to test and validate system performance, monitor live operations, and rapidly diagnose and resolve issues with minimal disruption. You will work across a large modern tech stack including SCADA, PLCs, IIoT technologies and industrial networking.

Requirements:

Balance development of new automation features with maintaining, troubleshooting, and improving existing production systems

Ensure system reliability and uptime for mission-critical operations running 24/7

High level of experience with Inductive Automation Ignition and willingness to learn new skills

Degree in engineering and/or equivalent industry experience with SCADA implementation in production environments

Proven experience collaborating within an engineering team to resolve design issues under operational constraints

Knowledge of I4.0/IIoT architectures and implementations

Fluent in programming concepts such as version control, object-oriented design, and agile development

Knowledgeable in Industrial Networking Protocols such as OPC-UA, MQTT, Modbus, RS485

About You?

Outcome focused with the ability to achieve results within a given time frame

Meticulous attention to detail

Company Description

About SEEK

SEEK’s portfolio of diverse businesses make a positive impact on a truly global scale. Our purpose is to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and help organisations succeed. We create world-class technology solutions to connect more people to relevant employment, education, small business and volunteer opportunities. We have a culture of high-performance in our workplaces and celebrate the diversity of our employees who contribute to the success of our organisation.

Life at SEEK

SEEK’s purpose is at the centre of everything we do. Our SEEK, which defines the way we work, is all about what makes us unique and a little bit different. Passion, Team, Delivery and Future are our principles that drive innovation and creativity. SEEK strives to support employee wellbeing by providing an amazing experience at work which led us to being named AFR BOSS Top 10 Best Places to Work in Technology (2021-2024). We are proud to work in an environment that's inclusive where everyone's unique ideas, experiences and perspectives are valued.

Our award-winning head office in Cremorne (just a 4 min walk from Richmond station) provides an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues. The building provides sweeping views of the city, a games area, sit and stand desks at every workstation, modern end-of-trip facilities and Thursday night drinks which gives our people an opportunity to connect in a social setting.

Job Description

About the Team

Pricing and Performance is a large team and is responsible for solving some of the most exciting and challenging problems for SEEK. You will help shape how jobs are priced and highlighted so more people find the right role, faster and see your work affect millions across APAC. You will join a team of 40 data scientists, engineers, and product managers working across three problem spaces. 

About the role 

As a Senior Software Engineer, you'll build and maintain production systems that power many of SEEK's AI-driven products. Your focus will be on engineering excellence, designing robust data pipelines, ensuring system reliability, and creating the infrastructure that enables data scientists to release their models confidently.

You'll work at the intersection of backend engineering and data platforms, solving challenging problems around scale, performance, and system design. This is a hands-on engineering role where you'll ship quality code, mentor teammates, and have real impact on products used by millions across APAC. 

Responsibilities 

Build scalable data and ML infrastructure, design systems that process large-scale data and support ML model deployment, from LLMs to bespoke models built for specialised problems 
Collaborate with Data Scientists, Product Managers, and Analysts to create impactful solutions in an agile environment 
Design and define software components that are robust, fault‑tolerant, and built for scalability and performance 
Take ownership of production services - ensuring reliability, uptime, and key SLAs are met 
Develop, test, and deliver systems that are high‑quality, secure, and fit for purpose 
Thrive in a dynamic, fast‑paced team where curiosity and continuous learning drive innovation 
Champion continuous delivery - removing blockers, improving processes, and enabling your teammates to deliver their best work 
Strive for technical excellence by balancing fast delivery with long‑term maintainability and platform health 
Qualifications

Skills and experience 

You don’t need to match our tech stack perfectly, we value your engineering mindset, flexibility, and drive to learn: 

You have 10+ years of strong backend expertise and a passion for data and machine learning engineering 
Proficiency in Python and/or Java, with solid software engineering fundamentals 
Building and maintaining data pipelines and working confidently with SQL 
Experience with Spark or Databricks for large-scale data processing 
Hands-on experience in AWS or other cloud environments 
Strong CI/CD and DevOps practices for robust, automated deployments 
Designing and operating machine learning pipelines in production 
Applying secure, testable, and maintainable coding practices while mentoring others on best standards 
Additional Information

Permanent Perks
At SEEK we offer:

Annual Performance Bonus Plan
Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role.
Paid and unpaid leave benefits including Personal Flexi Days and Volunteer Days, as well as the opportunity to purchase additional leave
Support for parents with 14 weeks paid primary carers leave and 2 weeks paid leave for partners
SEEK is committed to operating sustainably and is preparing for the impacts of climate change and the transition to a low-carbon future, and is working to minimise its environmental impacts which includes a long-term emissions reduction target of net zero by FY2050

Job Title: Technical Data and AI Product Manager
Ad Text:
Join a SaaS company that provides an AI-powered, cloud-based platform for builders and contractors to instantly assess property feasibility. The company services client globally. This is a fully remote position. 

About The Role
We’re looking for a Technical Data & AI Product Manager to join a fast growing SaaS company. This role is ideal for someone who can connect business needs, data opportunities, and emerging AI capabilities to deliver scalable, high-impact solutions.

You’ll work at the intersection of data engineering, AI/GenAI, and product strategy, defining what we should build, why it matters, and how it integrates into our platform. You’ll collaborate closely with engineers, data specialists, and other Product Managers to shape the future of the organisations AI-powered features and data-driven insights.

The ideal candidate has strong technical understanding (data pipelines, APIs, AI model capabilities), hands-on product experience, and the ability to bring structure and clarity in a fast-paced, evolving startup environment.

Key Responsibilities

Define and own the roadmap for data and AI/GenAI initiatives, from early discovery through delivery.
Translate business and user needs into data and AI-driven solutions, framing problems and hypotheses clearly.
Envision AI and GenAI use cases across company ecosystem — from automations to user-facing intelligence — and scope MVPs or spikes to validate feasibility.
Collaborate with data engineers to define and prioritize data pipelines, models, and infrastructure improvements.
Work closely with data analysts to ensure relevant KPIs, dashboards, and insights are delivered to stakeholders.
Partner with other Product Managers to understand business flows, identify where data sits, and ensure consistent, reliable data usage across the platform.
Partner with engineering and design to translate AI and data opportunities into user-centric features.
Define and monitor success metrics for AI and data products — ensuring outcomes are measurable and traceable to business impact.
Write clear user stories and technical requirements for data and AI-related projects.
Balance experimentation and delivery, ensuring short-term wins while building toward long-term AI maturity.
Communicate clearly across technical and non-technical stakeholders, simplifying complex ideas and progress updates.
Take strong ownership of your domain, working autonomously while keeping the broader team aligned.


Requirements

4+ years of Product Management experience, ideally in SaaS or technology environments.
Proven experience working with data, analytics, or AI/ML/GenAI initiatives in a product or technical capacity.
Strong understanding of data architecture concepts (data pipelines, APIs, integrations, SQL, ETL/ELT processes).
Experience collaborating with data engineers and analysts on delivering data products or AI features.
Solid grasp of AI and GenAI capabilities (LLMs, embeddings, retrieval, automation, NLP, etc.) and ability to scope practical use cases.
Comfort driving spikes and proofs-of-concept to validate technical feasibility before committing to full builds.
Excellent skills in problem framing, hypothesis testing, and prioritization.
Strong ability to self-organize, take ownership, and communicate effectively under pressure.
Experience working closely with engineering and design teams in Agile environments.
Proactive and pragmatic — balances innovation with feasibility.
Excellent written and verbal communication skills.
If interested, APPLY NOW for more details.

This role suits someone who enjoys building reliable data pipelines, working across cloud and on-prem platforms, and enabling high-quality, trusted data for reporting and analytics.

You’ll be responsible for designing and supporting data ingestion processes into an enterprise data warehouse, developing scalable ETL solutions, and ensuring data is accurate, accessible, and fit for purpose. The role involves close collaboration with analysts, technical teams, and business stakeholders to understand data requirements and deliver solutions aligned to business priorities.

Providing operational support and continuous improvement of data platforms

Proven experience as a Data Engineer in complex environments

Solid communication skills and the ability to work with non-technical stakeholders

Brunel has partnered with a leading organisation in the defence sector to offer an exciting opportunity for a Configuration Engineer to join on a permanent, full-time basis at their Henderson facility. This role is well suited to someone with a strong technical background in configuration management and PLM systems, who thrives in complex engineering environments.

Description

The Configuration Engineer supports the Configuration Management Team in executing and maintaining robust configuration management practices across a complex defence program. This role focuses on the technical implementation of configuration processes, data analysis, and system integration, ensuring accurate reporting and traceability of configuration items throughout the product lifecycle.

Key Responsibilities:

Collaborate with the Configuration Management Lead to implement and maintain CM processes aligned with ASDEFCON and defence standards.
Serve as the technical expert for PLM systems (Siemens Teamcenter), including data modelling, integrations, and automation.
Develop and maintain Configuration Status Accounting (CSA) reports and Baseline Reports using a variety of data solutions, scripting methods, and analytical tools.

Main Duties:

Develop and maintain Configuration Data by managing design and product baselines, change requests, variations and obsolescence using Teamcenter.
Administer and optimize the system landscape for configuration management tools including Teamcenter, TCRA, Jira, and Power BI.
Perform advanced data analysis to support configuration audits, change impact assessments, and baseline integrity checks.
Support Engineering Change Proposal (ECP) workflows and ensure accurate data traceability across digital systems.
Automate reporting and dashboarding solutions to provide real-time visibility into configuration status and metrics.
Assist in the preparation and execution of configuration audits, including data readiness and traceability validation.
Troubleshoot and resolve technical issues related to PLM integrations, data inconsistencies, and reporting errors

Profile

Degree in Engineering, Information Systems, Business Systems Analysis, or a related technical field.
Australian Citizenship is essential
Strong analytical mindset with attention to detail and data integrity.
Excellent communication skills for cross-functional collaboration and technical documentation.
Good understanding of IT system landscapes and infrastructure, including familiarity with server environments, scheduled tasks, and basic troubleshooting, to support configuration related operations and integrations.
Strong hands-on experience with PLM systems, especially Siemens Teamcenter.
Proficiency in SQL and Python for data extraction, transformation, and analysis.

Preferred

Solid understanding of configuration management principles and defence standards.
Demonstrated ability to work in complex digital environments with integrated systems and evolving processes.
Advanced skills in Power BI for dashboard creation and data visualization.

You will play a key role in shaping innovative data engineering solutions, working closely with clients to remove technical blockers and accelerate adoption of best practices across big data platforms.

The organisation is growing fast, has a strong global reputation, with an opportunity for growth and significant exposure to the Databricks team. If Databricks is a passion for you, this is an organisation that will have you working alongside some of the most experienced and strongest technical professionals in the space.

● Flexible working options, competitive remuneration, and a culture that values technical contribution and innovation.

About Us

LGT is the largest Private Banking and Asset Management group in the world to be owned by an entrepreneurial family. As the family office of the Princely House of Liechtenstein, we bring decades of experience in managing significant assets with care and expertise.

Solution Engineer (12‑Month Fixed-Term)

Location: Sydney CBD/ Melbourne CBD (Hybrid)

Role Overview

We are seeking a Solution Engineer to join our Engineering team within the broader Technology function. This role is pivotal in shaping the technology landscape that underpins our client experience, operational efficiency, and long‑term strategic growth.

As a Solution Engineer, you will translate business needs into scalable, secure, and cost‑effective technology designs. You will partner closely with stakeholders across the business and Group Technology to deliver integrated solutions that align with our global standards and local priorities.

Key Responsibilities

Provide hands‑on support during build, integration, and deployment phases, including prototypes, reference implementations, and technical troubleshooting.

Lead end‑to‑end solution architecture across the full project lifecycle from requirements and conceptual design through to build, testing, deployment, and transition to operations.

Partner with business stakeholders to understand needs, constraints, and strategic objectives, ensuring solutions are fit‑for‑purpose and aligned with long‑term goals.

Develop high‑level and detailed solution designs, including architecture diagrams, integration patterns, data flows, and security considerations.

Evaluate technologies and platforms, recommending options that balance cost, scalability, performance, and alignment with Group Technology standards.

Embed “security by design” principles into all architecture and design activities.

Collaborate with engineers, developers, and Group Technology teams to validate and refine solution designs.

Support functional and non‑functional testing to ensure solution integrity and performance.

Produce high‑quality documentation, runbooks, and knowledge‑sharing materials for operational teams.

Contribute to the technology strategy, design standards, and continuous improvement of engineering and delivery practices.

Essential Skills and Experience

Demonstrated hands‑on experience in building and developing technology solutions, including configuration, integration, and automation activities as required.

Deliver technical support and guidance throughout solution implementation, assisting in the resolution of design and build challenges.

Experience designing and architecting business‑critical systems in complex environments.

Broad knowledge of IT technologies, cloud platforms, integration patterns, and security principles.

Qualifications

Tertiary qualification in Information Technology, Computer Science, Engineering, or a related discipline.

5+ years’ experience in solution design, architecture, or technical consulting roles.

Certifications in cloud, architecture, or design frameworks (e.g., AWS, Azure, TOGAF) are advantageous.

Company Description

At Healthcare Australia (HCA), we are united by a shared commitment: to drive innovation and excellence in the healthcare sector. As Australia's largest specialist healthcare workforce provider, we are shaping the future of care through strategic transformation and a relentless focus on improvement. This is more than just a job; it is an opportunity to lead change that will create a profound and positive impact. 

Job Description

We have a new opportunity for an experienced Data Engineer to join our Technology team and play a pivotal role in building HCA’s new enterprise data platform.

This role is critical to the design, build, and operation of our data lake and analytics environment, leveraging Microsoft Fabric to deliver secure, reliable, and high-quality data across the organisation. Reporting directly to the CIO, you’ll work closely with product owners, BI developers, and operational teams to ensure data is ingested, transformed, and made ready for insight-driven decision making.

Your work will directly support HCA’s digital transformation agenda, data strategy, and privacy obligations across a complex healthcare environment.

We are open to this position being based in our Melbourne or Sydney offices.

Come help shape a modern data platform and also:

Design, build, and maintain scalable ETL/ELT data pipelines using Microsoft Fabric Data Factory, Lakehouse, and OneLake
Establish and manage HCA’s enterprise data lake / lakehouse architecture, ensuring performance, security, and governance
Ingest, cleanse, transform, and structure data from multiple ICT systems to support analytics and reporting
Configure and manage Fabric workspaces, capacities, security, and access controls in line with privacy requirements
Collaborate with BI teams, product owners, and stakeholders to deliver high-quality, analytics-ready datasets

Let’s talk about you!

As a Data Engineer, you’ll bring strong hands-on experience building modern data pipelines and working with data lake or lakehouse architectures. You’re comfortable operating in a regulated environment, have a strong focus on data governance and privacy, and enjoy collaborating with BI teams and business stakeholders.

Your resume will showcase your experience in designing and building ETL/ELT pipelines and hands-on experience with Microsoft Fabric (Data Factory, Lakehouse, OneLake, workspace management).  Naturally you’ll have a strong capability in SQL, with experience using PySpark and/or KQL for data transformation

Working alongside our CIO this role suits an Engineer with a strong understanding of data governance, privacy, and secure data handling in regulated environments

Microsoft certifications such as. Fabric Data Engineer Associate – DP-700 would be highly regarded!

Bring your passion to HCA and be rewarded with:

Hybrid working – work from home up to 2 days per week
Rewards Platform: Access to a comprehensive rewards and benefits platform 
Happy Birthday to you! The day off on your birthday each year 
The opportunity to help build a greenfield enterprise data platform and make your mark within a friendly, supportive, and growing organisation (more than 1,000 employees!)

If you have any questions, please contact Carly Currie (carly.currie@healthcareaustralia.com.au).

Veterans are encouraged to apply. At HCA we are committed to embracing diversity and committed to providing a safe working environment.

Are you a data science expert passionate about AI innovation and stakeholder influence? We’re seeking a Senior Data Scientist to drive cutting-edge AI advancements while working closely with executives and non-technical stakeholders to shape AI adoption and impact.
This role is ideal for someone who thrives at the intersection of technical excellence and business strategy, ensuring AI solutions deliver real value across the organisation.

About the Role
Join a rapidly growing AI-driven organisation at the forefront of innovation in LLMs, NLP, and Generative AI. This role is ideal for a hands-on data scientist who thrives in building scalable AI solutions, experimenting with state-of-the-art models, and driving real-world impact through applied research and engineering excellence. You’ll work across multi-cloud environments, collaborate with technical and business stakeholders, and help shape the next generation of intelligent systems.
Key Responsibilities
LLM & NLP Development – Design, fine-tune, and deploy advanced large language models (PEFT, LoRA, PPO) to solve complex business challenges.
GenAI & RAG Engineering – Build and optimise retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) pipelines, embedding models, and agentic AI architectures.
MLOps & Deployment – Implement scalable ML workflows with CI/CD, monitoring, benchmarking, and automation best practices across AWS, GCP, or Azure.
Collaboration & Influence – Work closely with cross-functional teams to translate AI research into production-ready solutions that deliver measurable outcomes.
Continuous Research – Stay ahead of emerging trends in LLMs, transformers, reinforcement learning, and generative architectures.
What You’ll Bring
4–8 years of hands-on experience in data science, AI, or machine learning, with deep knowledge of NLP and LLM applications.
Strong proficiency in Python, PyTorch, and SQL, plus experience with frameworks such as LangChain, Hugging Face, or LlamaIndex.
Practical experience building RAG pipelines, integrating vector databases (Pinecone, Weaviate, FAISS), and deploying solutions through Databricks, SageMaker, or Vertex AI.
Understanding of MLOps, monitoring, and feature store design, ensuring performance and reliability at scale.
Curiosity and drive to experiment with new architectures, delivering meaningful improvements to model capability and business value.
What’s in It for You
Contribute to cutting-edge AI initiatives in a fast-paced, high-impact environment.
Collaborate with talented engineers, researchers, and product leaders who share a passion for innovation.
Access modern tech stacks, flexible hybrid working, and opportunities to shape enterprise-level GenAI adoption.
Be part of a team that values curiosity, technical mastery, and solving real-world problems with AI.

If you’re a highly experienced AI professional who can influence at an executive level while delivering cutting-edge AI solutions, we’d love to hear from you. Apply now!

About Additive Assurance

At Additive Assurance, we're solving a major problem in metal 3D printing: ensuring parts are made right, every time. Companies in critical industries like aerospace and medicine use 3D printing to create everything from jet engine components to surgical implants. However, tiny, random flaws can cause these crucial parts to fail.

Our unique technology uses sensors and software to monitor the printing process in real-time, catching defects as they happen. This leads to safer parts, less waste, and greater trust in 3D printing technology. Your work will help make this advanced manufacturing technique a reliable, everyday tool for engineers worldwide.

The Role

We're looking for a versatile and resourceful Junior Machine Learning Engineer to join our small, hands-on team. You'll tackle a range of challenges involving unique industrial sensor data, with a primary focus on the deep learning models that power our defect detection.

This is a role for a true problem-solver. You won't just be tuning hyperparameters in a vacuum; you'll be responsible for the entire ML lifecycle—from designing data pipelines and training architectures for 3D segmentation to optimising models for the edge and integrating them into production code. This is a role for a builder; you'll be shipping solutions in a fast-moving environment where your work makes a tangible impact on physical manufacturing.

A Note On Our Culture: Is This Role For You?

We are a team of fast builders and tinkerers who thrive on rapid iteration and tangible results. We believe in moving quickly, learning from the results, and continuously improving.

To succeed in this role, you will need to learn quickly and adapt as you go. If you prefer a slower, more guided work environment, or if your passion lies more in theoretical research than in hands-on building and deployment, this might not be the role for you. We are looking for people who are driven by the process of creating, deploying, and seeing their solutions used in the real world.

What You'll Do

Design & Deploy: Train and refine deep learning models for classification and segmentation of unique sensor data.

ML Frameworks: Support the development of our ML framework, specifically focusing on image and 3D data.

Experiment at the Edge: Design and run experiments to push the performance of ML models on real-world hardware.

End-to-End Ownership: Learn and participate in the entire ML lifecycle, from data pre-processing through to model evaluation.

Collaborate: Work closely with our software engineering team to integrate models into our production software stack.

What You'll Bring

A Builder's Mindset: A genuine passion for machine learning and a strong desire to see your models solve real-world problems.

Technical Foundation: Solid knowledge of machine learning concepts, demonstrated through projects.

Deep Learning Tools: Hands on experience with frameworks like PyTorch or TensorFlow.

Python Proficiency: Strong familiarity with Python and its data science ecosystem (e.g., NumPy, Pandas).

Right to Work: You must have the right to work in Australia.

Bonus Points: Exposure to 3D data processing, computer vision, and software engineering practices (Git, Docker, Linux) is highly regarded.

What We Offer

Salary: Annual salary of $75,000 - $90,000 + super (pro-rata for part-time).

Invest in Your Growth: We provide dedicated, paid time for guided and self-directed learning to help you build a world-class foundation in ML.

Meaningful Equity: Through our employee share scheme, you'll have a real stake in our success.

The Mission: The opportunity to work on cutting-edge technology that is actively shaping the future of global manufacturing.

Collaborative Environment: A dynamic and flexible work environment at our Oakleigh office.

Ready to Join Us?

If you're a junior ML enthusiast who loves solving problems and wants to make a significant impact in a growing company, we would love to hear from you. Apply now to be part of our journey to revolutionise manufacturing!

As a software engineer, you will work on a specific project critical to Google’s needs with opportunities to switch teams and projects as you and our fast-paced business grow and evolve. We need our engineers to be versatile, display leadership qualities and be enthusiastic to take on new problems across the full-stack as we continue to push technology forward.

With your technical expertise, you will manage project priorities, deadlines, and deliverables. You will design, develop, test, deploy, maintain, and enhance software solutions.

Google's Global Network Security team are responsible for the full lifecycle of a massive, web-scale network that reaches from core data centers to edge locations, providing the foundation for services like Gemini, Gmail, Search, and YouTube, while also supporting cloud networking for Google Cloud Platform (GCP) customers and AI/ML initiatives.

Google Cloud accelerates every organization’s ability to digitally transform its business and industry. We deliver enterprise-grade solutions that leverage Google’s technology, and tools that help developers build more sustainably. Customers in more than 200 countries and territories turn to Google Cloud as their trusted partner to enable growth and solve their most critical business problems.

Work with the cross-functional team partners to understand their requirements and build the products to meet those requirements.

Your New Role 

Reporting to the Chief Platform Officer, the Head of AI and Automation Services is a senior leader responsible for enabling the Funds ambition to use technology as a differentiator for the future.

The Head of AI and Automation Services will work across the Fund, including Member and Investment domains and is responsible for ensuring that the design and implementation of AI and enabling colleagues to adopt AI across the Fund and deliver AI enabled outcomes for members.

The Head of AI and Automation plays a pivotal strategic role in advancing the Fund’s digital and AI automation maturity, operational resilience, and capacity for innovation.

Key duties include but are not limited to:

Thought leadership on the direction of AI, trends and identify opportunities for the Fund.
Champion the Fund’s enterprise AI & hyper automation strategy to optimise business processes, enhance operational capabilities, and drive digital transformation.
Provide visionary leadership, setting the direction for AI & hyper automation initiatives that align with the Fund’s long-term objectives and member-first philosophy. 
Collaborate with Executives, business stakeholders and IT leaders to ensure automation strategies are integrated with broader organisational goals. 
Understand the global AI governance and risk management practices to ensure that the Fund aligns to regulatory and industry guidelines.
Identify and assess emerging trends in AI, including GenAI, Agentic AI, machine learning (ML), power automation (PA), intelligent process automation (IPA), and their application to the Fund’s operations
Promote a culture of innovation and continuous improvement within the Technology Digital and Data domain and across the Fund.
Engage with internal and external stakeholders to identify AI and automation opportunities, manage expectations, and communicate progress and value delivered.
Ensure relevant legislative and organisational requirements are met; keep up to date on all key changes to relevant regulations.
Lead the AI & automation team to implement and scale new ways of working, and deliver outcomes at pace.

What You’ll Need   

Extensive experience (10+ years) in IT, digital transformation or process automation, with demonstrated leadership in large-scale AI and automation initiatives. 
Demonstrated track record of successful delivery of enterprise automation projects, including AI/ML, BPM, RPA and analytics solutions. 
Expert knowledge of AI and automation platforms (e.g., Microsoft Power Platform, Microsoft AI, OpenAI, ServiceNow, cloud technologies and other Gen AI services). 
Deep knowledge in data management and data practices.
Familiarity with data analytics, cybersecurity, compliance frameworks and COBIT/ITIL service management. 
Relevant certifications in automation, AI, and project management frameworks (e.g., Lean, Agile/Scrum, ITIL, Microsoft certifications) highly desirable. 
Proven ability to establish and manage Centres of Excellence (CoE), including governance, quality assurance and continuous improvement standards. 
Exceptional stakeholder engagement and communication skills, with experience influencing senior executives and preparing executive-level reports, business cases and dashboards.
